<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_EP14_MiniGoatsAndMiniSheep" s="332545">
  <T n="name">0x5F009C9D<!--Mini Goats and Mini Sheep--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP14\UI\Lessons\EP14_GoatSheep_Slide1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:49770b73c2e758e1</T>
      <T n="text">0x83A4401B<!--<b>Mini Goats and Mini Sheep</b> are a perfect addition to any ranch!\n\nPurchase them from:<ul><li><b>Phone's Home</b> section: <b>Call Ranch Animal Exchange</b></li><li><b>Ranch Community Board</b></li><li><b>Hay Now! Animal Feeder</b></li><li><b>Bits & Bales Mercantile</b> in New Appaloosa</li>--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP14\UI\Lessons\EP14_GoatSheep_Slide2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:49770b73c2e758e2</T>
      <T n="text">0x2EB40F01<!--Mini Goats and Mini Sheep require care of their <b>Hunger, Hygiene, and Attention</b> to keep their <b>Mood</b> up. The happier they are, the more you can earn from shearing and milking.\n\nHover over an animal to see the status of <b>Needs</b> and other information such as their <b>Happiness</b> and life stage.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP14\UI\Lessons\EP14_GoatSheep_Slide3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:49770b73c2e758e3</T>
      <T n="text">0xF533B051<!--<b>Hunger:</b> To feed these Ranch Animals, purchase a <b>Hay Now! Animal Feeder</b> in <b>Build Mode</b> or bottle feed them yourself. While you're there, buy some <b>Prairie Grass</b> so they can graze on their own.\n\n<b>Hygiene:</b> Give them a good brushing to keep them clean.\n\n<b>Attention:</b> Mini Goats and Mini Sheep are social creatures, so have a chat or give them a nice pet. If you succeed, surrounding Mini Goats and Mini Sheep will take notice and get Attention, too!--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP14\UI\Lessons\EP14_GoatSheep_Slide4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:49770b73c2e758e4</T>
      <T n="text">0xA14797A0<!--Mini Goats and Mini Sheep are more than adorable ranch companions! Mini Sheep can be sheared and Mini Goats can be milked once per day. As you earn their trust, they even will help with the garden and improve negative Mood.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP14\UI\Lessons\EP14_GoatSheep_Slide5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:49770b73c2e758e5</T>
      <T n="text">0xF2BEC8C4<!--If your Mini Goats and Mini Sheep are Unhappy for too long, they will run away to greener pastures. But don't worry! They'll give you a second chance and stay if you take better care of them.\n\nIf you are having trouble keeping up with them, hire a <b>Ranch Hand</b> to help out!--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP14\UI\Lessons\EP14_GoatSheep_Slide6.png">2f7d0004:00000000:49770b73c2e758e6</T>
      <T n="text">0x8C76EEE9<!--Life is precious and fleeting. Mini Goats and Mini Sheep will pass away from old age when the time comes. If you are not ready to part with your animal friends, go to the <b>Game Options</b> menu, select <b>Gameplay</b>, and turn off <b>Animal Aging</b>. Now you don't have to say goodbye!--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
